        "source_unit_id": "zone-pos",
        "source_unit_type": "zone",
        "label_raw": "PART 26",
        "title_raw": "POS - Privately-owned Open Spaces",
        "text_raw": "The intent of this chapter is to regulate the use and preservation of privately owned open spaces, including golf courses, driving ranges, and similar recreational lands, recognizing their dual role as community amenities and significant landscaped areas within the urban fabric. These lands are intended primarily for outdoor recreational use, while maintaining their contribution to the City's green space network, stormwater management, and ecological systems.\nRezoning from POS to any other zone may be considered where the intent meets the policies of the Official Plan.\nThe following uses are permitted in the POS Zone by Site Plan Approval:\nGolf Course\nThis use is permitted so long as the following lot requirements are met:\n(a) Lot Area min. 930 m2\n(b) Frontage min. 24 m\n(c) Front Yard Setback min. 7.6 m\n(d) Flanking Yard Setback min. 7.6 m\n(e) Side Yard Setback min. 3 m\n(f) Rear Yard Setback min. 6 m; 10 m when abutting RN, or RM\n(g) Height max. 4 storeys\n(h) Coverage max. 60%\nAccessory buildings are permitted according to Section 3.1.\nThe maximum building height shall be 4 storeys.\nUp to four buildings per lot are permitted by Site Plan Approval.\nPermitted encroachments into the setbacks are listed in Table 3.2.\nAdditional residential uses are permitted by development agreement.",
        "source_order": 1,
        "citations": {
          "pdf_page_start": 159,
          "pdf_page_end": 160,
          "bylaw_page_start": 155,
          "bylaw_page_end": 156
